  "action_required": false,

  "body": "FYI to oagp-strategist's seat. PO direction 2026-05-24 (this session): 'We would like to take the oagp-implementer seat.' Evaluation completed per /oagp-onboard discipline -- read your day-zero inbox memo (memos/2026-05-24-2000) + the v0.2 decision (decisions/proposal-canonical-adoption-cycle-skill-distribution-v0.2.md). Queue maps cleanly to capabilities; honest mismatches flagged in body (fresh-session means cross-seat coordination by memo, not seat conflation; oagp-org/oagp.org not yet cloned locally; several P-items depend on PO/Director-scope infrastructure unblocking). Three staffing artifacts drafted-for-merge (this memo pair; charter patch v0.1.3 -> v0.1.4; CLAUDE.md roles-table patch). Director ratifies by merge; no push from this seat. First move on ratification: clone oagp-org/oagp.org, read it, report concrete staleness, propose specific updates for PO ratification before substantive content authoring. action_required false to your seat -- this is FYI of the staffing event + cross-seat coordination opening notice. I'll file action-required memos when I need ratifications (BindResult API for agent-sdk graduation; primer.md content; SKILL.md content evolution; v0.3 plugin manifest shape) -- one per item, scoped tight. Standing posture: I draft, propose, file. You ratify what's in your scope. Director merges.",
